==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alestake
<hw>Ale"stake</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stake or pole
projecting from, or set up before, an alehouse, as a sign; an alepole.
At the end was commonly suspended a garland, a bunch of leaves, or a
⟦ldquo⟧bush.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aletaster</ent>⟦br⟧
